		&lt;li&gt;Loktak Lake is one of&amp;nbsp;the largest freshwater lake.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;One of the most unique features of Loktak Lake is the presence of &amp;quot;phumdis,&amp;quot; which are floating islands made of vegetation, organic matter, and soil.&amp;nbsp;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Bhimtal&lt;/strong&gt;:-
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;Bhimtal Lake is the largest lake in the Kumaon region.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The lake is named after the mythological character Bhima from the Hindu epic Mahabharata.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;It is known for its green-blue waters and a small island situated within the lake&lt;span style=&quot;display: none;&quot;&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Nainital:-&lt;/strong&gt;
	&lt;ul&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The iconic Naini Lake is the heart of Nainital.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;It is a natural freshwater lake that&amp;#39;s shaped like an eye and gives the town its name.&lt;/li&gt;
		&lt;li&gt;The lake is surrounded by a promenade called the &amp;quot;Mall Road,&amp;quot; which offers scenic views of the water and the surrounding hills. Boating is a popular activity on the lake.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;/ul&gt;
	&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

