&lt;p&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;display: flex;gap: 6px;align-items: center;&quot;&gt;&lt;img height=&quot;26px&quot; src=&quot;//cdn.testbook.com/resources/lms_creative_elements/key-point-image.png&quot; width=&quot;26px&quot; /&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;span style=&quot;vertical-align: middle;font-size: 21px;&quot;&gt;&lt;u&gt;Key Points&lt;/u&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;ul&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Pashto is an&lt;strong&gt; Iranian language&lt;/strong&gt; spoken primarily in &lt;strong&gt;Afghanistan and Pakistan&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;It is &lt;strong&gt;one of the two official languages of Afghanistan&lt;/strong&gt;, along with &lt;strong&gt;Dari&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Pashto&lt;/strong&gt; is also spoken by the &lt;strong&gt;Pashtun diaspora&lt;/strong&gt; in other countries around the world.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;The language has a &lt;strong&gt;rich literary tradition&lt;/strong&gt;, with &lt;strong&gt;poetry and prose&lt;/strong&gt; dating back centuries.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Pashto has its own unique script, known as the &lt;strong&gt;Pashto alphabet&lt;/strong&gt;, which is written from &lt;strong&gt;right to left&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;There are several dialects of Pashto, with the two main ones being&lt;strong&gt; Northern Pashto &lt;/strong&gt;and &lt;strong&gt;Southern Pashto&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;Pashto has been influenced by various other languages, including &lt;strong&gt;Persian, Arabic, &lt;/strong&gt;and &lt;strong&gt;English&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
	&lt;li&gt;It is an important language for understanding the culture, history, and society of the &lt;strong&gt;Pashtun people&lt;/strong&gt;.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;

